soldAS - My signs are everywhere
First home buyers, downsizers and investors will delight in this neat and tidy Dandenong property offering a light filled place to call home. Enjoy the community lifestyle of a well-planned villa estate, low body corporate fees and a great location walking distance to Hemmings Park, Dandenong North Primary, Dandenong High School, Dandenong Market, Plaza and Dandenong Hospital as well as easy access to trains, buses, Eastlink and the Monash Freeway.
Only around the corner from the soon to be Kaufland Supermarket on Gladstone Rd & Princes Highway that will definitely hype up the demand of properties in the area even more, this is a golden opportunity for one lucky buyer.
A practical design finished with neutral interiors delivers a home ready for new owners or tenants to move straight in to. A spacious, open plan kitchen, meals and living room form the inviting living spaces whilst two robed bedrooms, a laundry, central bathroom and separate WC complete the layout. Additional features of the home include ducted heating, a reverse cycle air conditioner, timber look cabinetry and feature pendant lighting.
Outside a private yard with large patio area, low maintenance gardens, single garage and tandem second car parking space add extra value to this brilliant home; an ideal first step, easy care downsize or smart addition to your investment portfolio!
• Light filled villa unit ready to move straight in – ideal first home, downsize or smart investment

• Private courtyard with large patio, low maintenance garden, single garage and second parking space
• Ducted heating, reverse cycle air conditioner, timber look cabinetry and feature pendants

Description:
A perfect start or unbeatable investment
Located in a highly desirable pocket of Dandenong, this gorgeous look like new brick veneer residence suiting all home buyers & investor's offers tranquil living and a fresh lifestyle.
Enjoying contemporary tones and an abundance of natural light, this appealing unit will delight with all the comforts and spaciousness a family could ever want. Entertaining family and friends will be an absolute must with the outdoor entertainment area.
Boasting a unique floor plan, as you walk straight into the home's open plan living and meals area you are greeted by two bedrooms tucked away to the side, each with built in robes as well as a family bathroom. Additionally, there is a separate laundry area that provides easy access to a spacious backyard. Fully renovated from top to bottom, Split System heating and cooling, gas cooking and a single carport top off this home.
You will be delighted by the serenity knowing that you're only moments away from Primary and Secondary Schools, bus stops, Short drive to Dandenong Shopping Centre, Market and Hospital,. Also offers you easy access to M1, East link, Princes Hwy and other major roads. Arrange to inspect before it is too late!

Description:
Hidden Gem! - in the heart of Dandenong.
Tucked behind a group of shops, this stylish residence situated in central Dandenong is suited for low maintenance living that will appeal to first home occupiers and investors alike. Within easy walking distance of Dandenong Plaza and market with buses, schools and trains also just minutes away.
This north facing townhouse features a big open plan lounge room and dining area. It has a modern kitchen with gas cooking and stainless-steel appliances together with loads of cupboard space and a breakfast bar.
There are 2 robed bedrooms upstairs including a family bathroom and a second living area to entertain the whole family. Other features include a separate laundry room and central bathroom and toilet downstairs, ducted vacuum, two split systems add to the comfort while an alarm adds peace of mind.
Outside there's a single garage with internal access and space in front to park another car plus an entertainer's courtyard with covered patio and garden shed.
In-Room Auction: Wednesday 28th November 2018 @ 6:30pm
Sandown Regency Motor Inn; 477 Princes Hwy, Noble Park
